ing, told jokes, went to the movies, and fell in love. Essays by Jonathan Okamura and Dawn Mabalon enlarge on Angeles’ account of early working-class Filipinos and situate her experience in the larger history of Filipino migration to the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aFilipino AmericanszCaliforniavDiaries. 0aFilipino AmericanszHawaiivDiaries. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh1 aRaymundo, Rizaline R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 amabalon, dawn bohulano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aokamura, jonathan y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 araymundo, alejandro s., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486521440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824865214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824865214/original  a978-3-11-056414-3  UHP eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066325-9  University of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK